Laurence D. Fink

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search



Laurence Fink





Born
Laurence Douglas Fink
November 2, 1952 (1952-11-02) (age 64)
Los Angeles, California, U.S.


Alma mater
University of California, Los Angeles


Occupation
Chairman & CEO of BlackRock


Political party
Democratic


Laurence Douglas "Larry" Fink (born 1952)[1][2] is an American financial executive. He is the chairman and CEO of BlackRock, an American multinational investment management corporation.[3] BlackRock is the largest money-management firm in the world with more than $5 trillion in assets under management by 2016.[4]



