In December 2016, Fink joined a business forum assembled by then president-elect Donald Trump to provide strategic and policy advice on economic issues.[17]
Personal life[edit]
Fink has been married to his wife, Lori, since the mid-1970s. The couple own homes in Manhattan, North Salem,[18] and Vail, Colorado. The couple have three children. Joshua, the eldest son, is CEO of Enso Capital, a hedge fund in which Fink owns a stake.[19] Fink is a lifelong Democrat.[4]
